Jr. Underwriter: Minneapolis, Minn.

Encompass User Support Specialist: Minneapolis, Minn.

Software Test Engineer: Fargo, N.D.
Mortgage Processor: Minneapolis, Minn.





What We’re Looking For
We hire people who will fit in well with our values and team. While every individual is different, the team qualities we seek include:



Ability to go above and beyond for our customers
Delivery of exceptional customer service
Willingness to be a team player
Habit of bringing a smile to work every day
Outgoing personality
Professional appearance
Desire to learn

Benefits You’re Looking For
Our competitive benefits package includes:



Health & dental insurance
Life & disability insurance
401(k) & profit-sharing plan
Employee Stock Ownership Plan
Year-end bonus
Paid vacation & holidays
Short-term disability
Long-term disability
Paid volunteer hours
Maternity, paternity & adoption leave
Bereavement leave
Clothing allowance
Wellness program
Employee Assistance Program
Special employee & family events
Opportunity to Pay It Forward to those in need

About Bell Bank
Bell Bank offers a fantastic work environment and a superior benefits package! For our employees, we provide everything you’d expect from a successful organization—support and training, competitive wages and an outstanding benefits package—and more. At Bell Bank, you’ll experience positive co-workers and team leaders, a fun and family-oriented atmosphere and opportunities to give back to the communities we serve.
 
Call us at 701-298-1550 and ask for human resources to find out more about career opportunities with our company. Thank you for considering Bell Bank for potential employment opportunities. We wish you every success.


Our Values & Bottom Line
As stewards, dedicated to the growth and reputation of this independently owned organization, we are committed to:



Promoting and sustaining our family atmosphere
Providing unequaled personal service to each and every customer
“Paying it forward” by giving back to the communities we serve

Bell Bank’s simple philosophy is embodied in our unique “Bottom Line” statement:


Happy Employees! Happy Customers!
Pay It Forward
Starting in 2008, Bell Bank gave employees a very special Christmas gift: the opportunity to “pay it forward” to people in need. It’s become a tradition continued each year. Every full-time employee receives $1,000 and every part-time employee $500 to give to an individual, family, organization or cause – a commitment totaling more than half a million dollars annually. To date, more than $8 million has been given to others less fortunate and to organizations that help build our communities.
 
Paying it forward is about compassionately helping others. Our employees’ Pay It Forward stories of giving will touch your heart.


Equal Opportunity Employer
Bell Bank complies fully with all federal, state and local employment laws and shall provide equal employment and advancement opportunities for all persons regardless of race, color, creed, religion, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, age, the presence of any mental or physical disability, status with regard to public assistance or marriage, or any other category protected by local, state or federal law.
Current Job Openings

Loan Officer Assistant: Phoenix, A.Z. Back to top
Company: Bell Mortgage
    Date posted: 7/17/17
    Status: Full-Time
Job Summary:
Under supervision and management of the Loan Officer, this position helps build a team with the goal of growing and expanding the team’s business while ensuring the highest possible level of customer service to the team’s clients.
Primary Duties:

Assist Loan Officer in managing new and existing loan volume.
Assist the Loan Officer with marketing their services.
Maintain customer database and assist in marketing to previous mortgage customer to increase volume.
Assist and maintain contact with clients, realtors, builders and others to maintain and deepen relationships to foster new business opportunities.
Keep informed of the trends and developments in the general real estate industry as well as the changing rules and regulations pertaining to all 1st mortgage origination. 
Provide high level of assistance to internal and external customers in person and on the phone. 
Review all documents for completeness and compliance with investor requirements.
Follow up on missing documents.
Maintain comprehensive understanding of the loan origination process and all functions within the processing and closing departments.
Ensure adherence to lending compliance requirements and internal procedures.
Perform other duties as assigned.
        

Job Skills Required:

Minimum of 2 years of mortgage banking experience preferred. 
Working knowledge of standard loan products in the industry and familiarity with underwriting guidelines.
Skills specific to mortgage origination and processing preferred.
Excellent customer service and communication skills.
Ability to function efficiently and effectively under deadlines and stress while maintaining a professional and mature profile.

Bell Bank Mortgage provides competitive compensation and an excellent benefits package. 
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank Mortgage, Human Resources, 5500 Wayzata Blvd Suite 140, Minneapolis, MN 55416 or email to askhr@bellbanks.com.


Processing Supervisor: Minneapolis, Minn. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank Mortgage
    Date posted: 7/17/17
    Status: Full-Time
Job Summary:
This position supervises a team of Loan Coordinators to ensure that new mortgage loan applications are processed and completed according to established policies/procedures and all Investor/Agency/Federal Guidelines.
Primary Duties:

Supervise the daily work of the Loan Coordinator Staff. This includes but not limited to performance reviews, counseling, motivating, training and monitoring daily work flow to ensure compliance with all Bell policies/procedures and all Investor/Agency/Federal guidelines.
Supervise and monitor all Bond loans to ensure compliance with agency guidelines. This includes but not limited to registration, compliance and HUD reviews.
Recommend procedure changes and improvements for the loan processing function.
Monitor, maintain and order supplies for the processing department.
Authorize payments on invoices received.
Process a low volume of loan files if needed.
Maintain up to date knowledge of all processing guidelines, Bell policies and procedures and Investor/Agency/Federal guidelines.
Provide prompt and courteous customer service to all internal/external clients.
Respond to any and all audit exceptions pertaining to the Loan processing function.
Work with other department supervisors to ensure/maintain effective communication.
Prepare estimated monthly closed loan projections.
Work with loan officers and processing staff in problem solving. Help them to prevent issues.
Hold monthly/quarterly processing staff meetings to review memos, problems, changed, etc.
Participate in various projects and feedback sessions to positively impact workflow, policies/procedures and system enhancements
Provide a positive work environment to invite staff participation and contribution to the development of a high level of service quality. Coach, mentor and raise the level of talent throughout the department
        

Job Skills Required:

Thorough understanding of all Agency/Investor/Federal Mortgage Banking guidelines.
Background in all areas of Mortgage process (origination, processing, underwriting, closing, post-closing).
Minimum three years of supervisory experience in Mortgage Banking.
Demonstrate ability to effectively manage/monitor the performance of others and provide effective feedback.
Capacity to adapt to ever changing processes, requirements, guidelines and environment.
Good communication skills to be able to effectively train and develop others.
Excellent customer service skills. 
Ability to successfully manage many tasks and deadlines as well as willingness to set and enforce deadlines for others.
Ability to work under pressure and maintain a high level of professionalism.
Demonstrate a “can do” attitude.
Attend all regulatory, industry and Bell required meetings and trainings.
Ability to function efficiently and effectively under deadlines and stress while maintaining a professional and mature profile.
Ability to work well with people with diversified personalities.

Bell Bank Mortgage provides competitive compensation and an excellent benefits package. 
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank Mortgage, Human Resources, 5500 Wayzata Blvd Suite 140, Minneapolis, MN 55416 or email to askhr@bellbanks.com.


User Provisioning Specialist: Fargo, N.D. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank
    Date posted: 7/14/17
    Status: Full-time
The User Provisioning Specialist position provisions user access by creating, modifying, and deleting user accounts and application access. This position configures and deploys hardware, including PCs, laptops, thin clients, printers, and phones. This position answers, troubleshoots, and logs incoming calls to the IT Department regarding both hardware and software from both internal and external customers. The User Provisioning Specialist ensures the continued integrity of the Bank’s information resources and assists in strengthening technical measures to protect bank resources and business electronic information. This position follows IT policies and procedures covering protocols, applications, networks, client, and server systems and shares backup responsibilities for the other team members on the EIS team.

    A two-year degree in Computer Science/Information Systems is required. Course work in computer networking, and business-related courses, or equivalent knowledge and skills, are desired. Candidates must have an in-depth knowledge of Microsoft client-based products (e.g. Windows 7, Office  2010), Trend Micro antivirus, and Windows Deployment Services. Successful candidates will have an intermediate knowledge of Active Directory, file and print servers, strong hardware background working with PCs, printers, and peripherals, and a solid understanding of networking, Citrix and vmWare.
    
Ability to work weekends and/or off hours as necessary to meet clients’ needs is required.

    Bell Bank provides an excellent benefits package.
    
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank, 3100 13th Ave. SW, Fargo, ND, 58103 or email to hr@bellbanks.com.


