Program Manager: Minneapolis, Minn. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank Mortgage
    Date posted: 6/27/17
    Status: Full-Time
Job Summary:
This individual is responsible for the development and implementation of mortgage systems strategies which support the business strategies in a core business division.  Working with the leadership of the assigned business division, this individual is responsible for developing schedule, budget, and staffing projections to accomplish the desired projects.  Once the strategy is developed, this individual must oversee the project portfolio to ensure they secure resources from all necessary departments in the company to complete projects in accordance with corporate priorities.
Primary Duties:

Responsible for development and implementation of systems strategies in a core business area.
Deep understanding of core business areas workflow and processes.
Regularly interacts with business unit’s senior management to analyze needs and integrate into overall business plan.
Responsible for development of budgets, timetables, and staffing. Manages costs and risks within area of responsibility.
Working with the assigned project teams, develop implementation plans for projects or tasks and ensure all planning steps are completed.
Aide in designing, developing and maintaining secure applications.
Work with other Business Leaders, Program Managers, and CIO to architect and align corporate computer system strategies 


Demonstrate skill in accessing, preparing, and using information as relevant to position and be able to present this information when required.
Consider impact on other departments when making technology decisions or recommendations.
Work with outside vendors and third parties to assist with procurement, issue management, and other items as needed.

Leadership Abilities:

Define and delegate work responsibilities with clear, consistent expectations and outcomes.
Demonstrate effectiveness in maintaining a well-organized operation to ensure the efficiency and accuracy of the work and information flow; monitor procedures and implement corrective actions as required.
Demonstrate the ability to take charge, take unpopular stands, if necessary, and face difficult situations.
Facilitate and foster change within the Bell Bank systems.
Demonstrate the ability to adapt to different types of personalities within the Bell Bank system.

Job Skills Required:

Degree in information technology or related field and a minimum of 8+ years of information technology experience.
Mortgage industry experience preferred.
Leadership experience with proven ability to efficiently lead and manage people and projects are desired.
This position also requires knowledge and experience in a variety of software design and development practices including traditional and agile methodologies, object oriented programming, N-Tiered architecture, multilayered applications, quality control, database, and security.
Strong verbal and written communication skills.

Bell Bank provides competitive compensation and an excellent benefits package. 
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank Mortgage, Human Resources, 5500 Wayzata Blvd Suite 140, Minneapolis, MN 55416 or email to askhr@bellbanks.com.


Underwriting Supervisor: Minneapolis, Minn. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank Mortgage
    Date posted: 6/21/17
    Status: Full-Time
Job Summary:
This position manages a team of 8-10 underwriters and will counsel underwriting staff on current and proposed loan submissions, providing high level of customer service. This position will mentor underwriting staff on difficult loan submissions and manage underwriting team capacity to ensure turn time expectations are met. Fifty percent of time will be managing people and working on delegated tasks.  Fifty percent of time will be spent underwriting loans.
Primary Duties:

Provide leadership, support and guidance to underwriting staff.
Underwrite conventional and/or government loans in accordance with all agency and investor guidelines and standards. May also be responsible for portfolio transactions.
Respond to all agency, investor, and internal audits to defend and support decisions for current and aged loan files for both your own work and the work of your team members.
Manage underwriting capacity by distributing daily work to team members. Identify when a team member’s work needs to be reassigned and execute the reassignment to ensure underwriting turn times are being met as a team.
Provide underwriting capacity coverage for absent team members.
Provide content for monthly underwriting team meetings and effectively communicate agenda items in a meeting setting.
Work ad hoc projects as assigned by senior leadership.
Work with Bell production staff to explain agency/investor guidelines when discussing or reviewing appraisals, credit submissions, and scenario questions.
Complete comprehensive review of entire loan package, from credit through appraisal through required documentation, to issue final underwriting decision.
Perform other duties as assigned.
        

Job Skills Required:

Five plus years’ general underwriting experience.
Three plus years of leadership experience in an underwriting production environment.
Thorough understanding of all agency and investor underwriting policies.
Ability to thoroughly review all conventional and/or government loan submissions and to independently make prudent lending decisions based on program guidelines.
Ability to review residential collateral (including condos) per agency and investor policies.
Ability to work efficiently and effectively under deadlines and stress while maintaining a professional and mature profile.

 
Bell Bank Mortgage provides competitive compensation and an excellent benefits package. 
 


Please send application & resume to Bell Bank Mortgage, Human Resources, 5500 Wayzata Blvd Suite 140, Minneapolis, MN 55416 or email to askhr@bellbanks.com.


Facilities Maintenance Technician: Fargo, N.D. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank
    Date posted: 6/20/17
    Status: Full-time

    This position assists the Facilities Maintenance Manager in all work relating to all aspects of Bank owned or leased buildings and grounds including, but not limited to the maintenance, repair and upkeep of Bank property. The Facilities Maintenance Technician will be actively involved in the performance of related work as required. Travel is required. The position requires versatility, attention to detail and good communication skills.
    

    Substantial knowledge of various phases of building construction, building maintenance and repair including mechanical systems, site management, janitorial work and office renovation is required. The successful candidate will have knowledge of a variety of maintenance and trade skills and uses. Bell Bank offers an excellent benefit package.
    
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank, 3100 13th Ave. SW, Fargo, ND, 58103 or email to hr@bellbanks.com.




