Underwriter: Minneapolis, Minn. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank Mortgage
    Date posted: 6/9/17
    Status: Full-Time
Job Summary:
This position completes conventional and/or government (HUD/VA/USDA) underwriting reviews in accordance with agency, investor and appraisal guidelines in a timely manner insuring compliance, quality and meeting closing schedules. This position will also counsel production and processing staff on current and proposed loan submissions, providing high level of customer service.
Primary Duties:

Underwrite conventional loans in accordance with all agency and investor guidelines and standards.
Respond to all agency, investor and internal audits to defend and support decisions for current and aged loan files.
Work with Bell production staff to explain agency/investor guidelines when discussing or reviewing appraisals, credit submissions and scenario questions.
Complete comprehensive review of entire loan package, from credit through appraisal through required documentation, to issue final underwriting decision.
Complete all underwriting reviews in a timely manner to meet proposed closing schedules and turn-time expectations.
Remain informed of all mortgage insurance program guidelines and offerings.
Know, understand, and live the company values and bottom line.
Perform other duties as assigned.
        

Job Skills Required:

Five years’ mortgage underwriting experience required.
Proficient knowledge of industry standard computer programs.
Thorough understanding of all agency and investor underwriting policies.
Ability to thoroughly review all conventional and government loan submissions and to independently make prudent lending decisions based on program guidelines.
Ability to review residential collateral (including condos) per agency and investor policies.
Ability to work efficiently and effectively under deadlines and stress while maintaining a professional and mature profile.
Ability to manage multiple tasks and deadlines simultaneously.
Excellent written and verbal communication skill to provide exceptional customer service.

Bell Bank Mortgage provides competitive compensation and an excellent benefits package.
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank Mortgage, Human Resources, 5500 Wayzata Blvd Suite 140, Minneapolis, MN 55416 or email to askhr@bellbanks.com.




Personal Banking Officer/Assistant Manager: Northeast Metro, Minn. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank
    Date posted: 6/9/17
    Status: Full-Time
Job Summary:
This position retains and expands existing customer personal deposit and loan relationships and acquires new customers by selling our various products. This position assists with service and sales to professional and executive clients, along with credit and deposit support, which may include consumer underwriting, along with documentation and credit administration for personal loans. This position is responsible for efficient, effective management of the office. 
Primary Duties:

Leadership/Supervisory:


Supervise office and serve as a contact to ensure building, grounds and equipment are properly maintained.’
May supervise office personnel.
Must be able to work flexible hours as scheduled.


Customer Service and Customer Retention:


Counsel customers regarding financial matters, advising them on products and rates, suggesting a strategy to obtain the best results based on individual desires and resources.
Serve as one of the primary contacts for Private Banking Department when clients come into the bank and/or over the phone.
Resolve customer problems, obtaining information, researching records and following up on details to resolve the matter to the customer’s satisfaction, whenever possible.
Assist with the opening of all depository accounts and cross-sale of other ancillary products and services. Ensure service standards are met. 


Business Development:


Develop business by calling on potential customers outside of the Bank.
Participate in various professional associations and community activities to enhance the Bank’s visibility and to further personal development.


Sales Programs:


Actively participate in the Ask Program.
Attend Quarterly Retail Sales Meetings.
Prepare preliminary client correspondence and customized professional client presentation materials to support sales and marketing efforts. 


Training / Development:


Attend and actively participate in training sessions as scheduled.
Attend and actively participate in meetings as scheduled.


Production:


Sell bank products and services through personal contact and direct mail including loans, checking, savings, certificate of deposits, individual retirement accounts, and other retail banking services.
Open business and personal accounts, preparing all permanent records.
Solicit, originate, underwrite and close consumer loans. Manage loan portfolio with emphasis in the growth of the portfolio.
Interview loan applicants, collect and analyze financial and related data to determine the general creditworthiness of the prospect and the merits of the specific loan request.
Actively sell credit life and disability insurance on all qualified loan customers.
Continue to enhance cross-selling skills and techniques. 
Increase customer relationships by cross-selling to include phone and/or letter contact to existing customers for additional services.
Cross-sell all products and services to new customers
Responsible for the daily handling of overdrafts on assigned customer accounts and make decisions on accounts where the officer is not available.
Keep technical exception report to a minimum.


Compliance and Regulatory Guidelines:


Establish and negotiate, within the framework of the Bank’s loan policy, terms under which credit will be extended, including the costs, repayment method, repayment schedule and collateral requirements.
Complete online compliance testing quarterly.
        

Job Skills Required:

A minimum of three (3) years of consumer or commercial banking experience.
Excellent judgment and problem solving skills and ability to work independently.
Thorough knowledge of office operations to coordinate the daily functioning of the office and to diffuse and resolve employee and customer problems.
Complete familiarity with the Bank’s savings, checking, and lending policies and guidelines, as well as specific loan programs, qualifications, insurance, and so on to provide full savings and loan services.
Interpersonal skills necessary to conduct business development calls to area agencies and deal with potential savings and loan customers.
Working knowledge of loan and deposit documentation.
Good working knowledge of rules, regulations and internal policies and practices relating to retail loan underwriting and documentation.
This position produces high-quality, professional work that is accurate, complete, and fulfills the intended purpose for presenting a positive image to clients.
Excellent written and communication skills.
Proficiency with computer technology.
Ability to deal with multiple tasks and deadlines.
Effective time management and organizational skills and the ability to prioritize multiple projects and tasks, and consistently meet deadlines.
Ability to be flexible and adapt well to change. 

Bell Bank provides competitive compensation and an excellent benefits package.
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank, Human Resources, 5500 Wayzata Blvd Suite 140, Minneapolis, MN 55416 or email to askhr@bellbanks.com.



IT Security Administrator: Fargo, N.D. or Minneapolis, Minn. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank
    Date posted: 5/19/17
    Status: Full-time
Bell Bank is seeking candidates for an IT Security Administrator in Fargo or Minneapolis. If you like to work with people in a family atmosphere, enjoy great benefits and provide unequaled personal service to every customer, consider a career with Bell Bank.
The IT Security Administrator ensures the secure operation of the in-house computer systems, servers, and network connections. Duties will include serving as the Engineering team’s incident response coordinator to enable mitigation, prevention, or event/incident resolution, either directly or indirectly with the assistance of solution experts. This role will be involved with enterprise IT Governance practices and procedures including regular reporting, general housekeeping of Enterprise infrastructure, security and audit recommendation research / fulfillment, and overall responsibility for said program. 
A B.A. in the field of computer science and / or 6 to 8 years of equivalent work experience is required. Certifications in the following areas are preferred: CompTIA Security+; Microsoft Certified Systems Administrator: Security, GIAC Information Security Fundamentals; CISSP: CISA. The successful candidate will have a broad hands-on knowledge of firewalls, intrusion detection systems, anti-virus software, data encryption, and other industry-standard techniques and practices. Candidates must have the ability to work flexible hours to maintain computer hardware and software within the Bell Bank infrastructure, to include after hours and weekends, as needed.
Bell Bank provides an excellent benefits package. 
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank, 3100 13th Ave. SW, Fargo, ND, 58103 or email to hr@bellbanks.com.






Jr. Underwriter: Minneapolis, Minn. Back to top
Company: Bell Bank Mortgage
    Date posted: 5/19/17
    Status: Full-Time
Job Summary:
 
Position will work closely with Underwriters and the Collateral team for Bell Mortgage.  Work collaboratively with and take direction from SVP of Operations, VP of Underwriting, Collateral Risk Manager, UW Supervisors and Mortgage Review Analyst.  This role is intended to function as a versatile floater for all underwriting tasks which will include clearing conditions, clearing loan purchase pends, analyzing appraisals, evaluating collateral reconsideration requests,  conducting analysis on income/credit reviews, general research and backing up the UW Assistant .  This position offers an expansive opportunity for growth in an Underwriting career path.
 
 
Primary Duties:

Analyze and complete underwriting resubmission requests
Act as point of contact for underwriting group to support, analyze and respond to pre-purchase investor delivery pends. 
Review and analyze appraisals to meet investor guidelines. 
Evaluate collateral reconsideration requests in the absence of the Collateral Risk Manager or in the circumstances of overflow.This responsibility will work closely with the Collateral Team, appraisers, and Underwriters.
Conduct income/credit reviews and provide supportive analysis to meet investor guidelines.
Manage UW Support mailbox and direct questions to the appropriate team member when assistance is needed.Manage response time to 8 business hours or less. 
Complete fraud vendor reviews on contract underwritten files. 
Work with Bell production staff to explain agency/investor guidelines when discussing or reviewing appraisals, credit submissions and scenario questions.
Work closely with all departments within organization to help identify and implement efficient and effective procedures to ensure sound lending decisions and high level customer service.
Maintain awareness of changing economic and industry conditions, new trends and developments in the local and national real estate mortgage markets.
Perform other duties as assigned.

Job Skills Required:

1-2 years mortgage underwriting experience required.
Correspondent lending experience preferred.
Appraisal underwriting experience preferred.
Overall understanding of economic and real estate markets from the locations where company originates loans.
Ability to manage multiple tasks and deadlines simultaneously.

Bell Bank Mortgage provides competitive compensation and an excellent benefits package.
Please send application & resume to Bell Bank Mortgage, Human Resources, 5500 Wayzata Blvd Suite 140, Minneapolis, MN 55416 or email to askhr@bellbanks.com.




